{{ 'dev-video-promo-banner.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'dev-video-promo-banner.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
{%- comment -%}
  JS is required: the Brief's Interactivity type is "modal (video playback)" — pattern (a),
  static poster background + a play button that opens the video in a lightbox.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .video-promo-banner {
    /* Brand params (Design Brief → Brand Params table).
       --container-max is intentionally absent and --section-px is 0: this section is
       full-bleed at both breakpoints (Brief, Note 1 — the media row starts at x=0 and
       spans the whole frame). The only width constraint is a max-width on the text block. */
    --section-px: 0px;

    /* Typography — desktop */
    --font-heading-size: 38px;
    --font-heading-weight: 500;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;
    --font-body-size: 18px;
    --font-body-weight: 500;
    --font-body-lh: 1.4;
    --font-button-size: 18px;
    --font-button-weight: 700;
    --font-button-lh: 1.4;

    /* Typography — mobile (from the Mobile artboard, not a scale factor) */
    --font-heading-size-m: 28px;
    --font-body-size-m: 16px;
    --font-button-size-m: 16px;

    /* Spacing */
    --spacing-sm: 8px;
    --spacing-md: 16px;
    --spacing-lg: 32px;
    --spacing-lg-m: 24px;
    --pt-scale-m: 0.6; /* 80px desktop → 48px mobile */

    /* Media tile */
    --tile-min-h: 500px; /* identical at both breakpoints (Brief, Note 4) */
    --tile-pt: 32px;
    --tile-pb: 32px;
    --tile-px: 24px;
    --tile-p-m: 24px;
    --bg-position: center;

    /* Text block */
    --text-max: 410px;
    --text-max-m: 327px;

    /* CTA button */
    --button-px: 24px;
    --button-py: 18px;
    --button-px-m: 18px;
    --button-py-m: 12px;
    --button-radius: 60px;
    /* Fixed, like every other button on the site. No section lets a merchant recolour one. */
    --cta-text-color: #333333;

    /* Play button */
    --play-btn-size: 62px;
    --play-btn-padding: 19px;
    --play-btn-radius: 60px;
    --play-icon-size: 24px;

    /* Modal */
    --modal-overlay: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85);
    --modal-max-w: 960px;
    --modal-px: 24px;

    /* Motion. The same asymmetry the PDP's guide drawers use: the lightbox takes its time arriving
       and leaves briskly, which is what makes it read as an object rather than a div being shown.
       The JS reads these back out (parseFloat on the computed value), so keep them in ms. */
    --modal-in: 480ms;
    --modal-out: 300ms;
    --ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
    --ease-in: cubic-bezier(0.55, 0, 1, 0.45);
  }
</style>

{%- liquid
  assign hosted_video = section.settings.video
  assign external = section.settings.video_external_url

  assign embed_url = ''
  if external != blank
    if external.type == 'youtube'
      assign embed_url = 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/' | append: external.id | append: '?autoplay=1&rel=0'
    elsif external.type == 'vimeo'
      assign embed_url = 'https://player.vimeo.com/video/' | append: external.id | append: '?autoplay=1'
    endif
  endif

  assign has_video = false
  if hosted_video != blank or embed_url != blank
    assign has_video = true
  endif

  comment
    Poster fallback. The background image is optional, so when it is empty the banner takes its
    poster from the video itself rather than rendering an empty tile: an uploaded video carries a
    preview_image, and YouTube exposes a thumbnail derived from the video id. Vimeo publishes no
    thumbnail URL that can be built without an API call, so a Vimeo-only banner still needs an image.
  endcomment
  assign poster = section.settings.background_poster_image
  if poster == blank
    assign poster = hosted_video.preview_image
  endif
  assign poster_alt = poster.alt | default: '' | escape

  assign poster_fallback_url = ''
  if poster == blank and external.type == 'youtube'
    assign poster_fallback_url = 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/' | append: external.id | append: '/maxresdefault.jpg'
  endif
-%}

<div
  class="video-promo-banner"
  style="
    --bg: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
    --color: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
    --accent: {{ section.settings.accent_color }};
    --pt: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
    --pb: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
  "
>
  <div class="video-promo-banner__tile">
    <div class="video-promo-banner__media">
      {%- if poster != blank -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          lazy, not eager: this banner sits ~2000px down the homepage, and the poster is the
          heaviest asset on it. Eager put it in the same fetch round as the hero — the LCP element —
          for a tile nobody has scrolled to yet. Nothing here is measured by JS, so there is no
          reason it has to arrive before it is visible.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          This poster was the heaviest asset on the homepage, for three separate reasons.

          1. CROP. The tile is --tile-min-h: 500px tall at BOTH breakpoints, full-bleed wide, and
             the poster is object-fit: cover — so everything past 500px of height was cropped away
             by the browser after being downloaded. Asking for width: 3200 off a 1920x3413 source
             made the 800w entry 800x1422: 1422px of image for a 500px box. Passing height + crop
             moves the crop to the CDN so each entry matches the box it lands in. The rendered
             result is identical; the browser was already cropping to exactly this.

          2. ART DIRECTION. One aspect cannot serve both breakpoints — the box is ~0.82 wide-to-tall
             at 412 and ~2.88 at 1440 — and a single srcset had to satisfy the taller one, which is
             what inflated the desktop entries too. Hence two sources.

          3. ENCODING. Shopify encodes PNG sources almost losslessly. Measured at identical output
             dimensions, bytes per pixel: PNG source 0.275, JPEG source 0.046 — same CDN, same
             format, 6x the weight. This source is a PNG whose alpha channel is FULLY OPAQUE, so
             the cost bought nothing. format: 'jpg' is what unlocks `quality`; image_url rejects it
             on a PNG outright ("quality can't be used with ext png"). The delivered format does
             not change — browsers still get WebP by content negotiation.

             75 was chosen by looking, not by taste: at 2x zoom on the fine branch detail, where
             WebP artefacts show first, q80/q75/q70 are indistinguishable from Shopify's default.
             PSNR against the untouched original drops 1.7dB for 34% fewer bytes.

          Two hard limits, both learned the expensive way:

          Neither srcset goes past 1920w. Ask Shopify to crop wider than the source and it silently
          drops the crop and returns the UNCROPPED image — width=2600&height=903&crop=center comes
          back 508x903 at the original 0.5625 aspect, 162KB, which the browser then cover-crops
          again. It renders correctly, which is exactly why it survived the first pass.

          The mobile list stops at 1100 because the tall crop is expensive: 1536x1864 is 435KB,
          worse than the original this replaced. Decorative background, cover-cropped everywhere —
          the extra density buys nothing anyone can see.

          Measured on the CDN, before -> after:
            mobile 824    291KB -> 150KB
            desktop 1440  (was picking a 2600w entry) -> 84KB
            desktop 1920                              -> 115KB
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <picture>
          <source
            media="(min-width: 769px)"
            srcset="
              {{ poster | image_url: width: 1000, height: 347, crop: 'center', format: 'jpg', quality: 75 }} 1000w,
              {{ poster | image_url: width: 1440, height: 500, crop: 'center', format: 'jpg', quality: 75 }} 1440w,
              {{ poster | image_url: width: 1920, height: 667, crop: 'center', format: 'jpg', quality: 75 }} 1920w
            "
            sizes="100vw"
          >
          {{
            poster
            | image_url: width: 1100, height: 1334, crop: 'center', format: 'jpg', quality: 75
            | image_tag:
              loading: 'lazy',
              widths: '400, 600, 824, 1100',
              sizes: '100vw',
              alt: poster_alt,
              class: 'video-promo-banner__poster'
          }}
        </picture>
      {%- elsif poster_fallback_url != blank -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Not a Shopify-hosted image, so image_tag cannot build it — the YouTube thumbnail is a
          plain remote URL. maxresdefault is 1280x720 for every video that has it.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <img
          class="video-promo-banner__poster"
          src="{{ poster_fallback_url }}"
          alt=""
          width="1280"
          height="720"
          loading="lazy"
        >
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    <div class="video-promo-banner__content">
      {%- if section.settings.show_play_button -%}
        <button
          class="video-promo-banner__play"
          type="button"
          aria-label="{{ 'Play video' | escape }}"
          {% if has_video %}
            data-video-open
            aria-haspopup="dialog"
            aria-expanded="false"
          {% endif %}
        >
          {%- comment -%}
            "Icon/Outline/play-solid" — exported from Figma (I45031:4301;34806:63342;23710:41236
            desktop / I44821:5480;44821:5504;34806:63342;23710:41236 mobile) by the Assets stage to
            .figma-assets/video-promo-banner/play-icon-{desktop,mobile}.svg. Both exports are
            byte-identical; the path data below is pasted verbatim from them. Verified by
            `node .claude/tools/svg-fidelity.mjs --section video-promo-banner`.
            The Figma layer is misnamed "Icon/Outline/plus" — the artwork is a solid play triangle
            (Brief, Note 2). Rendered 24x24 against a 24x24 viewBox, so the aspect matches exactly.
            Figma fills it #333333 = Neutral/700 = the --cta-text-color default, so it is bound to
            currentColor rather than hardcoding the hex (CSS hard rule).
          {%- endcomment -%}
          <svg
            class="video-promo-banner__play-icon"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            aria-hidden="true"
            focusable="false"
          >
            <path d="M16.7519 11.168L7.5547 5.03647C6.89015 4.59343 6 5.06982 6 5.86852V18.1315C6 18.9302 6.89014 19.4066 7.5547 18.9635L16.7519 12.8321C17.3457 12.4362 17.3457 11.5638 16.7519 11.168Z" fill="currentColor"/>
          </svg>
        </button>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- if section.settings.heading != blank or section.settings.subheading != blank -%}
        <div class="video-promo-banner__text">
          {%- if section.settings.heading != blank -%}
            {%- comment -%} inline_richtext: already safe HTML from Shopify — never escape it. {%- endcomment -%}
            <h2 class="video-promo-banner__heading">{{ section.settings.heading }}</h2>
          {%- endif -%}

          {%- if section.settings.subheading != blank -%}
            <p class="video-promo-banner__subheading">{{ section.settings.subheading }}</p>
          {%- endif -%}
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        The CTA is a BLOCK, not a section setting (Brief → Structure: "Merchant-addable
        element → BLOCK: CTA link button"). Only one exists in the design, so limit: 1.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
        {%- if block.type == 'cta_button' and block.settings.label != blank -%}
          {%- liquid
            assign cta_link = block.settings.link
            if cta_link == blank
              assign cta_link = routes.root_url
            endif
          -%}
          {%- render 'dev-button',
            variant: 'filled',
            label: block.settings.label | escape,
            link: cta_link,
            class: 'video-promo-banner__button',
            attrs: block.shopify_attributes
          -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
  </div>

  {%- if has_video -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      A native <dialog>, opened with showModal(). It is not a div wearing role="dialog": the element
      brings the focus trap, Escape, the ::backdrop layer and inertness of the page behind it for
      free, all of which the hand-rolled version was missing — from the old modal you could Tab
      straight out of the video and onto the page underneath.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <dialog
      class="video-promo-banner__modal"
      aria-label="{{ 'Video' | escape }}"
      data-video-modal
    >
      {%- comment -%}
        tabindex="-1" so the JS can land initial focus here on open instead of on the close button.
        showModal() otherwise focuses the first focusable child (the ×), which iOS Safari rings with a
        focus-visible outline — a white circle around the ×. Keyboard users still Tab to the × normally.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="video-promo-banner__modal-inner" tabindex="-1">
        <button
          class="video-promo-banner__modal-close"
          type="button"
          aria-label="{{ 'Close video' | escape }}"
          data-video-close
        >
          <svg
            class="video-promo-banner__modal-close-icon"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            aria-hidden="true"
            focusable="false"
          >
            <line x1="5" y1="5" x2="19" y2="19"/>
            <line x1="19" y1="5" x2="5" y2="19"/>
          </svg>
        </button>

        {%- comment -%}
          `image_size` sets the poster. Without it video_tag reaches for Shopify's own preview
          thumbnail at its `_small` cut — a ~100px image stretched across a 960px player, which is
          why the first frame arrived visibly blurry. 1280x is the widest the player is ever drawn.

          preload stays `none`: this sits below the fold on the homepage and the source is a 4.5Mbps
          HD file, so every visitor should not pay for it. The JS warms it on intent instead — the
          moment the pointer or focus reaches the play button — so the click still plays at once.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if hosted_video != blank -%}
          {{
            hosted_video
            | video_tag:
              controls: true,
              playsinline: true,
              preload: 'none',
              image_size: '1280x',
              class: 'video-promo-banner__video'
          }}
        {%- elsif embed_url != blank -%}
          <iframe
            class="video-promo-banner__iframe"
            title="{{ 'Video' | escape }}"
            data-src="{{ embed_url }}"
            src="about:blank"
            allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture"
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    </dialog>
  {%- endif -%}
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Video promo banner",
  "tag": "section",
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Video promo banner",
      "blocks": [{ "type": "cta_button" }]
    }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "cta_button",
      "name": "CTA button",
      "limit": 1,
      "settings": [
        { "type": "text", "id": "label", "label": "Button label", "default": "Our Story" },
        { "type": "url", "id": "link", "label": "Button link" }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "max_blocks": 1,
  "settings": [
    { "type": "header", "content": "Content" },
    {
      "type": "inline_richtext",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "default": "Trees into duvets – who would've thought?"
    },
    {
      "type": "inline_richtext",
      "id": "subheading",
      "label": "Subheading",
      "default": "See the difference in under 60 seconds."
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "background_poster_image",
      "label": "Background image",
      "info": "Fills the banner. Leave empty to use the video's own preview frame (uploaded video or YouTube)."
    },
    {
      "type": "video",
      "id": "video",
      "label": "Video",
      "info": "Plays in a lightbox when the play button is clicked."
    },
    {
      "type": "video_url",
      "id": "video_external_url",
      "label": "Video link",
      "accept": ["youtube", "vimeo"],
      "info": "Used only when no uploaded video is set."
    },
    { "type": "checkbox", "id": "show_play_button", "label": "Show play button", "default": true },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Colors" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "background_color", "label": "Background", "default": "rgba(0,0,0,0)" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "text_color", "label": "Text color", "default": "#FFFFFF" },
    {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "accent_color",
      "label": "Accent color",
      "info": "Button and play button background.",
      "default": "#FFFCF4"
    },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Spacing" },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_top",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "label": "Padding top",
      "default": 80
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_bottom",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "label": "Padding bottom",
      "default": 0
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
